  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="User Needs">
  <data key="d0">User Needs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The specific requirements or queries from users that RAG systems aim to address with tailored responses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Existing RAG Systems">
  <data key="d0">Existing RAG Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Current Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems that have significant limitations such as reliance on flat data representations and inadequate contextual awareness.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Flat Data Representations">
  <data key="d0">Flat Data Representations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A limitation of existing RAG systems that restricts their ability to understand and retrieve information based on intricate relationships.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Contextual Awareness">
  <data key="d0">Contextual Awareness</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A quality that existing RAG systems often lack, leading to fragmented answers that do not capture complex inter-dependencies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Enhanced Retrieval Efficiency">
  <data key="d0">Enhanced Retrieval Efficiency</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A key challenge addressed by LightRAG, aiming to improve speed over graph-based knowledge structures to reduce response times.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rapid Adaptation To New Data">
  <data key="d0">Rapid Adaptation To New Data</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A key challenge addressed by LightRAG, ensuring the system remains relevant in dynamic environments by quickly adapting to updates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chunking">
  <data key="d0">Chunking</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A technique that breaks down large external text corpuses into smaller segments to enhance the accuracy of information retrieval in RAG systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LightRAG Github Repository">
  <data key="d0">LightRAG Github Repository</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The online location where the open-source LightRAG model is available.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LIGHTRAG: Simple And Fast Retrieval-Augmented Generation">
  <data key="d0">LIGHTRAG: Simple And Fast Retrieval-Augmented Generation</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The title of the paper proposing the LightRAG model, authored by Zirui Guo, Lianghao Xia, Yanhua Yu, Tu Ao, and Chao Huang.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0747de8554c174a10ea77615f403b7d8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="API Call">
  <data key="d0">API Call</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An API call is a request made by an application to an API, used for accessing features or data. LightRAG optimizes this process to a single call.&lt;SEP&gt;A mechanism used by the Custom GPT (Reasoning Layer) via Actions to communicate with external services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3bd0191ab33228d4256b14cc82b68e6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770308052</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Newly Added Data">
  <data key="d0">Newly Added Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Newly added data refers to new datasets or information incorporated into a system, which GraphRAG manages inefficiently, while LightRAG integrates seamlessly.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Community Structure">
  <data key="d0">Community Structure</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The community structure is a component within GraphRAG that must be dismantled and regenerated when new data is added, incurring high costs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LLMs (Large Language Models)">
  <data key="d0">LLMs (Large Language Models)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Large Language Models are systems whose inputs are enhanced by RAG systems and whose capability to interpret graph-structured data is a focus of research.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="External Sources">
  <data key="d0">External Sources</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">External sources are where RAG systems retrieve relevant information to enhance LLM inputs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Current RAG Approaches">
  <data key="d0">Current RAG Approaches</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Current RAG approaches typically embed queries in a vector space to find context vectors, often relying on fragmented text chunks and limiting global information capture.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vector Space">
  <data key="d0">Vector Space</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A vector space is where current RAG approaches typically embed queries.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Context Vectors">
  <data key="d0">Context Vectors</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Context vectors are found in a vector space by current RAG approaches to retrieve relevant information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fragmented Text Chunks">
  <data key="d0">Fragmented Text Chunks</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Fragmented text chunks are small, disconnected pieces of text that many current RAG methods rely on.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Top-K Contexts">
  <data key="d0">Top-K Contexts</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Top-k contexts refer to a limited number of most relevant contexts retrieved by many current RAG approaches.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Global Information">
  <data key="d0">Global Information</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Global information refers to comprehensive, overarching data that current RAG methods often limit their ability to capture.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dynamic Updates">
  <data key="d0">Dynamic Updates</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Dynamic updates refer to the capability to incorporate new information and changes into a system effectively, a feature often lacking in existing graph-based approaches.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Graphs">
  <data key="d0">Graphs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Graphs are a powerful framework for representing complex relationships, especially in the context of Large Language Models.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e05809f164c96a85130a50b30fcfdc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768751034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
